15,01Saturday Night in Suburbia

15,01Halting movement
15,01and the cars snake around
15,01each other
15,01in their fruitless endeavor
15,01to find a resting place.
15,01The mist on the windows
15,01impairs my vision
15,01and foot meets brake
15,01each time
15,01light is refracted
15,01off the night rain
15,01into my sight.
15,01The search grows longer
15,01the obstacles
15,01more tiring
15,01maneuvering around
15,01bodies of cars, buildings, and people.
15,01Annoyed by the arduous task
15,01my car stops
15,01far from the destination
15,01but my walk is short
15,01albeit longer than my patience.
15,01My arrival is greeted
15,01by the squawking herald of the crowd's commotions.
15,01And the journey begins
15,01once more
15,01as I search for a deserted
15,01place to seat my tired body.
15,01Stuck in this continent
15,01of commercialism, conformity
15,01and corporate attitudes,
15,01I'm looking for more
15,01than a physical place to be
15,01I'm here with my pen
15,01to find my place within
15,01myself,
15,01but the searching does not
15,01end.

15,01!virago!
